    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-12-06T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-12-06T17:00:00-05:00" n="265"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d265">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">862i.01/61a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wallace</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="13" xml:id="d265fn13">See last paragraph for instructions
                        to repeat to Rome as no. 233.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-12-06T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 6, 1920—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1674. For the Ambassador referring our 1625 November 9, 4 p.m.<note n="14"
                        xml:id="d265fn14">See footnote 2, <ref target="#pg_263">p. 263</ref>.</note>
                    For transmission to the Foreign Office.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>I have the honor to refer to my communication of November [12] setting forth
                        the views of my Government relative to the status of the island of Yap. I
                        have received instructions to bring to your attention certain additional
                        considerations with reference to this same matter, from which may be
                        obtained a better understanding of the position of my Government.</p>
                    <p>[Here follows, <hi rend="italic">mutatis mutandis</hi>, the communication to
                        the British Government contained in telegram no. 1199, December 4, 1920, to
                        the Ambassador in Great Britain, beginning with the words “There would
                        appear.”]</p>
                </quote>
                <p>Transmit above to Rome as Department’s 233 for delivery <hi rend="italic">mutatis
                        mutandis</hi> to Foreign Office referring Department’s 213 to Rome November
                        9.<note n="14" xml:id="d265fn15">See footnote 2, <ref target="#pg_263">p.
                            263</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
